The World Health Organisation is deploying more than 40 experts in South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Sixteen team members from the WHO surge team have arrived in South Africa. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize says they’ll be providing fresh eyes to the country's COVID-19 situation. Mkhize was speaking as he welcomed the first members of the World Health Organization surge team to South Africa. WATCH: WHO Surge Team arrives in South Africa They'll be helping government with its COVID-19 response. "The 16 team members have now arrived in the country and when the team is complete there will be 43. Those that are already with us have begun an orientation period to ensure there is optimal alignment of programmes... they will look at our situation with fresh eyes," said Mkhize. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.